companyProfile.companyDescription: Tata Motors Limited is an India-based global automobile manufacturer of cars, utility vehicles, pick-ups, trucks, and buses, offering a range of integrated, smart, and e-mobility solutions. The Company's segments include Automotive and Others. The Automotive segment consists of four reportable sub-segments: Tata Commercial Vehicles, Tata Passenger Vehicles, Jaguar Land Rover and Vehicle Financing. Its automotive business includes all activities relating to development, design, manufacture, assembly and sale of vehicles including financing thereof, as well as sale of related parts, accessories and services. The Others segment consists of information technology services and insurance broking services. With operations in India, the United Kingdom, South Korea, Thailand, South Africa and Indonesia, the Company markets its vehicles in Africa, the Middle East, Latin America, Southeast Asia, and the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) countries.

recentNews.intro: The Harrier EV was unveiled by Tata Motors at  ?21.49 lakh, it competes with other electric SUVs like Hyundai Creta EV, Mahindra XEV 9e and BYD Atto 3 in the market.
recentNews.imagecaption: The Tata Harrier EV is the Indian car manufacturer's flagship EV. (Photo by Indranil Mukherjee / AFP)

recentNews.headline: Hybrids vs EVs: New advisory for Delhi fleet operators adds fresh fuel to fire
recentNews.intro: The debate over hybrid versus electric vehicles has heated up with Delhi's air quality monitoring body's latest advisory asking commercial fleet operators to avoid conventional fuel vehicles, without clearly defining 'clean vehicles'.
recentNews.imagecaption: Some experts argue that hybrid vehicles and electric vehicles complement each other, and would ultimately help in the growth of the EV sector. But other experts argue only pure electric vehicles be incentivized if India wants to promote zero-emission vehicles. (AI-generated image)

recentNews.headline: Tata Motors share price rises 2%, looks set to snap 3-day losing streak; should you buy?
recentNews.intro: Tata Motors' share price increased nearly 2% in intraday trade on June 4, recovering from a three-day decline. Tata Motors' share price has lost about 22 per cent over the last year, hitting a 52-week high of  ?1,179.05 on July 30 last year and a 52-week low of  ?542.55 on April 7 this year.
recentNews.imagecaption: Tata Motors' share price is witnessing profit booking after a healthy 12 per cent gain in May.

recentNews.headline: Stock Picks: Sagar Doshi suggests Tata Motors, LTIMindtree, ZEEL shares to buy today - 4 June
recentNews.intro: Stock Picks: Sagar Doshi of Nuvama Professional Clients Group recommends these three stocks today - Tata Motors Ltd, LTIMindtree Ltd, and Zee Entertainment Enterprises Ltd (ZEEL).
recentNews.imagecaption: Stock Picks: Sagar Doshi of Nuvama Professional Clients Group recommends these three stocks today - Tata Motors Ltd, LTIMindtree Ltd, and Zee Entertainment Enterprises Ltd (ZEEL).

recentNews.headline: Tata Motors plans a premium push as competition intensifies in EV space
recentNews.intro: Tata Motors launched the EV variant of its Harrier SUV on Tuesday at an ex-showroom price of  ?21.49 lakh. The launch of the new EV comes at a time when Tata Motors' lead in the electric vehicles segment is being aggressively challenged by MG Motor India, Mahindra & Mahindra (M&M) and Hyundai.

recentNews.headline: Mahindra cements 2nd position as Tata Motors, Hyundai?s sales continue to lag behind
recentNews.intro: Compared to other car makers who have varied offerings such as hatchbacks, sedans and SUVs, Mahindra?s portfolio largely has SUVs, which have benefited from consumers? preference for larger cars.
